CASING.Name: CASING_NAME
CASING.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
CASING.Description_Text:
A lightweight metal product, heavily used in the manufacture of <TECHNOLOGY>starship parts<> and <TECHNOLOGY>deployable technology<>. A mainstay of the construction industries of all known primary species.

Crafted from <EARTH>Ferrite Dust<>.

NANOTUBES.Name: NANOTUBES_NAME
NANOTUBES.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
NANOTUBES.Description_Text:
Metres and metres of high capacity <FUEL>carbon nanotubes<>.

Their high tensile strength and mild conductivity make these a key component in many <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

CARBON_SEAL.Name: CARBON_SEAL_NAME
CARBON_SEAL.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
CARBON_SEAL.Description_Text:
A high-performance <FUEL>carbon seal<>, able to withstand both the harsh interstellar environment and the rigours of intensive, high-energy industrial use.

User is advised to regularly check seal integrity after installation.

MICROCHIP.Name: MICROCHIP_NAME
MICROCHIP.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
MICROCHIP.Description_Text:
A compact, <TECHNOLOGY>low-heat microchip<>. Assembled from processed <STELLAR>Chromatic Metal<>, created from one of several specialised terrain metals.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

HYDRALIC.Name: UI_HYDRALIC_NAME
HYDRALIC.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
HYDRALIC.Description_Text:
Specialist <TECHNOLOGY>wiring and control threads<>, this flexible material allows the transmission of power and signals, as well as offering direct manipulation of remote components.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

COMPUTER.Name: UI_COMPUTER_NAME
COMPUTER.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
COMPUTER.Description_Text:
An extremely fast <TECHNOLOGY>advanced processing unit<>. Allows real-time solving of otherwise impossible calculations. However, protection against decoherence is not guaranteed.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

MAGNET.Name: UI_MAGNET_NAME
MAGNET.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
MAGNET.Description_Text:
An electromagnetic <TECHNOLOGY>frequency oscillator<>, able to function in a wide-range of conditions thanks to both ferrous and non-ferrous magnetic properties.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

MIRROR.Name: UI_MIRROR_NAME
MIRROR.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
MIRROR.Description_Text:
A specialist optical component. Employing an impossibly polished surface, this mirror is able to selectively filter different wavelengths of light, changing its reflective pattern based on nearby magnetic fields.

Used in the creation of a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

BIO.Name: UI_BIO_NAME
BIO.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
BIO.Description_Text:
A specialist <TECHNOLOGY>biological catalysation device<>.

This unit takes advantage of naturally occurring enzymes in order to facilitate increased energy yields and faster processing in a wide range of <TECHNOLOGY>advanced technologies<>.

REPAIRKIT.Name: UI_REPAIR_KIT_NAME
REPAIRKIT.Subtitle: UI_REPAIR_KIT_SUB
REPAIRKIT.Description_Text:
A highly useful piece of <STELLAR>survival technology<>, the Repair Kit allows damaged equipment to be quickly and efficiently restored to working order.

While repairing a piece of techology, the Repair Kit can be applied to any damaged subcomponent in place of the usual requirements.

PRODFUEL2.Name: FUELGEL3_NAME
PRODFUEL2.Subtitle: FUELGEL_SUB
PRODFUEL2.Description_Text:
Emergency <FUEL>life support fuel<>.

Synthesised from <TECHNOLOGY>rocket fuel crystals<> and <FUEL>carbon<>, this gel offers a temporary boost to life support systems. Long-term impact on user's lungs is currently unknown.

POWERCELL.Name: POWERCELL_NAME
POWERCELL.Subtitle: POWERPROD_SUB
POWERCELL.Description_Text:
Convenient and optimised power storage unit. Used in a wide variety of <COMMODITY>defensive<> and <COMMODITY>hazard protection<> systems.
 
Constructed by fusing <EARTH>Ferrite Dust<> with underground <TECHNOLOGY>Cobalt<>. Frequently found ready-made in cylindrical metal containers.

SHIPCHARGE.Name: UI_SHIPCHARGE_NAME
SHIPCHARGE.Subtitle: POWERPROD_SUB
SHIPCHARGE.Description_Text:
A power storage unit optimised for use in <COMMODITY>starship defensive systems<>.
 
<SPECIAL>Tritium<>-fuelled capacitors provide quick-release charge for the <TECHNOLOGY>Deflector Shield<>, but would overload smaller-scale equipment.

JELLY.Name: FUEL_JELLY_NAME
JELLY.Subtitle: FUELGEL_SUB
JELLY.Description_Text:
A faintly-glowing jelly. Its gentle light and soft wobble belie the fact that this sticky gel is both highly toxic and highly flammable. Skin contact is to be avoided at all costs.

Synthesised from <TECHNOLOGY>Di-hydrogen<>.

LAUNCHFUEL.Name: LAUNCHFUEL_NAME
LAUNCHFUEL.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
LAUNCHFUEL.Description_Text:
Highly reactive solid-state fuel, required to fuel <TECHNOLOGY>Starship Launch Thrusters<>.

Created from crystallised <TECHNOLOGY>Di-hydrogen<>, found in blue deposits on all worlds.

SUBFUEL.Name: UI_SUBFUEL_NAME
SUBFUEL.Subtitle: UI_SUBFUEL_SUB
SUBFUEL.Description_Text:
A high thermal energy fuel, contained within a standardised fuel cell. Used to fuel the <TECHNOLOGY>Humboldt Drive<> that powers the Nautilon submarine.

Created with a mix of organic compounds (<FUEL>Carbon<> and <TRADEABLE>cyto-phosphates<>) and localised mineral <TRADEABLE>salts<>.

GRENFUEL1.Name: GRENFUEL1_NAME
GRENFUEL1.Subtitle: GRENFUEL1_SUBTITLE
GRENFUEL1.Description_Text:
Densely-packed fuel capsule for use in the <TECHNOLOGY>Plasma Launcher<>.
 
Contained highly-pressurised electro-thermal energy for use in land disruption grenade technology.

AMMO.Name: AMMO_PROD_NAME
AMMO.Subtitle: AMMO_PROD_SUB
AMMO.Description_Text:
Advanced munition fragments, constructed to fit Universal Multi-Tool Standard 07/FF1.

Easily inserted into the <TECHNOLOGY>Boltcaster<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Pulse Spitter<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Scatter Blaster<> via the Multi-Tool clip reloading system.

AM_HOUSING.Name: AM_HOUSING_NAME
AM_HOUSING.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
AM_HOUSING.Description_Text:
Secure antimatter containment device, required before <FUEL>Antimatter<> can be safely secured as <FUEL>Warp Cells<>.

Rebound <FUEL>Oxygen<> forms a protective gas pocket, preventing the antimatter from reacting with the surrounding casing.

ANTIMATTER.Name: COMMODITY6_NAME
ANTIMATTER.Subtitle: CRAFTPROD_SUB
ANTIMATTER.Description_Text:
Contained negative matter and baryogenesis antiparticles.
 
The vast energy potential of antimatter makes it highly valuable. 95% of existing antimatter consumption is in the powering of <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrives<>.

<FUEL>WARNING<>: uncontained usage is not recommended.

HYPERFUEL1.Name: HYPERFUEL1_NAME
HYPERFUEL1.Subtitle: HYPERFUEL1_SUBTITLE
HYPERFUEL1.Description_Text:
This <FUEL>antimatter-based fuel<> is one of the few power sources capable of meeting the incredible energy requirements of a <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrive<>.

Secured within a robust housing, the cell is guaranteed paradox-free during FTL travel.

HYPERFUEL2.Name: HYPERFUEL2_NAME
HYPERFUEL2.Subtitle: HYPERFUEL2_SUBTITLE
HYPERFUEL2.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>high-capacity<> <FUEL>antimatter-based fuel<>, this cell harnesses an internal black hole generator to power <TECHNOLOGY>starship hyperdrives<> across multiple warp jumps.

Cell walls are specially designed to reflect any reality paradoxes back towards the heart of the unit, where they generate additional power.

ALLOY1.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_1_NAME
ALLOY1.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY1.Description_Text:
A lightweight and highly malleable alloy. Crafted from <EARTH>Paraffinium<> and <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<>.

In high demand on the Galactic Trade Network due to its utility in the construction of planetside outposts and facilities.

ALLOY2.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_2_NAME
ALLOY2.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY2.Description_Text:
A popular metal alloy with a wide variety of uses. 'Dirty Bronze' has shed its scientific name in favour of the popular term for its colour.

Crafted from <EARTH>Pure Ferrite<> and <EARTH>Pyrite<>.

ALLOY3.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_3_NAME
ALLOY3.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY3.Description_Text:
Combined neutral alloy with uses that range from pharmacology all the way to heavy industry. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Ammonia<>.

Forms the backbone of galactic alloy trading.

ALLOY4.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_4_NAME
ALLOY4.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY4.Description_Text:
Pure Ferrite alloy. Crafted from <EARTH>Pure Ferrite<> and <EARTH>Uranium<>.

Used extensively in starship freighter construction due to its sheer strength. A hardcore material popular on the Galactic Trade Network.

ALLOY5.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_5_NAME
ALLOY5.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY5.Description_Text:
Highly prized and lustrous alloy. Popular with traders of all known primary galactic races. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Phosphorus<>.

Easily recognisable by its bright red glow and strong magnetic field.

ALLOY6.Name: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_6_NAME
ALLOY6.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_SIMPLE_SUBTITLE
ALLOY6.Description_Text:
Soft workable alloy favoured by artisans throughout the known galaxy. Crafted from <EARTH>Ionised Cobalt<> and <EARTH>Dioxite<>.

A popular trading good, with many galactic shipping paths devoted to its sale and transport.

ALLOY7.Name: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_1_NAME
ALLOY7.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_SUBTITLE
ALLOY7.Description_Text:
Advanced and durable alloy primarily used in starship hull construction and deep-space exploration drone technology.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Herox<>, <SPECIAL>Dirty Bronze<> and <SPECIAL>Lemmium<>.

ALLOY8.Name: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_2_NAME
ALLOY8.Subtitle: UI_ALLOY_COMPLEX_SUBTITLE
ALLOY8.Description_Text:
Advanced light metal alloy traded throughout the galactic Outer Edge. Often used in the interiors of trading shuttles to reduce weight as they ascend from planets with high gravitational fields.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Aronium<>, <SPECIAL>Magno-Gold<> and <SPECIAL>Grantine<>.

ACCESS1.Name: ACCESS1_NAME
ACCESS1.Subtitle: ACCESS1_SUBTITLE
ACCESS1.Description_Text:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.

Provides access to low level restricted areas and outpost systems.

ACCESS2.Name: ACCESS2_NAME
ACCESS2.Subtitle: ACCESS2_SUBTITLE
ACCESS2.Description_Text:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to mid-tier restricted areas and outpost systems.

ACCESS3.Name: ACCESS3_NAME
ACCESS3.Subtitle: ACCESS3_SUBTITLE
ACCESS3.Description_Text:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to high level restricted areas and outpost systems.

MIND_ARC.Name: UI_MINDARC_NAME
MIND_ARC.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MIND_ARC.Description_Text: A strange piece of technology, a gift from beyond the stars. It shimmers in a way that suggests it is not fully in this world.

SOUL_ENGINE.Name: UI_SOULENGINE_NAME
SOUL_ENGINE.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
SOUL_ENGINE.Description_Text:
A powerful organic computing unit.

A glitching beat drives this miracle circuit, performing cycle after cycle in an endless, furious loop of calculation.

BP_SALVAGE.Name: BP_SALVAGE_NAME
BP_SALVAGE.Subtitle: BP_SALVAGE_SUB
BP_SALVAGE.Description_Text:
The salvageable heart of some ancient technology. Unreadable in its current form.

These databanks can be spent at a <TECHNOLOGY>Construction Research Unit<> and used to research new <STELLAR>Construction Blueprints<>.

FACT_TOKEN.Name: UI_FACT_TOKEN_NAME
FACT_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_FACT_TOKEN_SUB
FACT_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A portable data unit, compatible with most <STELLAR>planetary fabricator facilities<>.

Once access has been gained to a central control terminal, the Override Unit can divert the facilities resources towards researching new product recipes.

FRIG_TOKEN.Name: UI_FRIG_TOKEN_NAME
FRIG_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_FRIG_TOKEN_SUB
FRIG_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A technology module harvested from the remains of a large interstellar starship. May be collected from <STELLAR>freighter crashsites<> or salvaged during <STELLAR>frigate expeditions<>.

Useless in its current form, a <TECHNOLOGY>Research Station<> aboard your freighter may be able to convert it into useable technology.

SHIP_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_SHIP_INV_TOKEN_NAME
SHIP_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_SHIP_INV_TOKEN_SUB
SHIP_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A technology module harvested from the remains of a <STELLAR>salvaged starship<>. May also be collected from <STELLAR>freighter crash sites<> or salvaged during <STELLAR>frigate expeditions<>.

Can be used to expand starship storage capacity at the Space Station's <TECHNOLOGY>Starship Outfitter<>.

FREI_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_FREIGHT_INV_TOKEN_NAME
FREI_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_FREIGHT_INV_TOKEN_SUB
FREI_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A technology module harvested from the remains of an <STELLAR>abandoned freighter<> found floating in space. May also be salvaged during <STELLAR>frigate expeditions<>.

Pre-packed nano-expanders fill out this portable unit and graft it to an existing freighter, increasing its <STELLAR>inventory capacity<>. Apply at your freighter's <TECHNOLOGY>Upgrade Terminal<>.

WEAP_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_WEAPON_INV_TOKEN_NAME
WEAP_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_WEAPON_INV_TOKEN_SUB
WEAP_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
A flexible upgrade circuit, compatible with all <STELLAR>person Multi-Tools<>.

This module can be wired into a Multi-Tool at a Space Station <STELLAR>Multi-Tool Upgrade Rack<>, granting the user more space in the Multi-Tool's internal layout to add further upgrades or technology specialisations.

SUIT_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_SUIT_INV_TOKEN_NAME
SUIT_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_SUIT_INV_TOKEN_SUB
SUIT_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text:
An advanced survival technology module that allows expansion of a user's <STELLAR>Exosuit Storage<>.

Pre-packed nano-expanders create stablised sub-warp voids within the Exosuit, increasing its <STELLAR>inventory capacity<>. Apply this augmentation at the Exosuit upgrade terminal on board a <STELLAR>Space Station<>.

ALIEN_INV_TOKEN.Name: UI_ALIEN_INV_TOKEN_NAME
ALIEN_INV_TOKEN.Subtitle: UI_ALIEN_INV_TOKEN_SUB
ALIEN_INV_TOKEN.Description_Text: An additional storage nodule<> for Sentient<> starships. Upon hatching, the parasite inside this sac is grafted upon the vessel, exchanging the use of its cavernous innards for vital nutrients from the host. Use FE_ALT1<><> to trigger growth and begin the hatching process<>.

ALIEN_TECHBOX.Name: UI_ALIEN_ALLTECHBOX_NAME
ALIEN_TECHBOX.Subtitle: UI_ALIEN_ALLTECHBOX_SUB
ALIEN_TECHBOX.Description_Text: A writhing sac of genetic fluid, designed to foster the creation of new bio-infused technology<> for a sentient starship<>. The embryo will grow into bio-technology upgrade<>. Begin biogenesis<> with FE_ALT1<><>.

FRIGATE_FUEL_1.Name: UI_FREIGHTER_FUEL_1_NAME
FRIGATE_FUEL_1.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
FRIGATE_FUEL_1.Description_Text:
A small barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

FRIGATE_FUEL_2.Name: UI_FREIGHTER_FUEL_2_NAME
FRIGATE_FUEL_2.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
FRIGATE_FUEL_2.Description_Text:
A large barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

FRIGATE_FUEL_3.Name: UI_FREIGHTER_FUEL_3_NAME
FRIGATE_FUEL_3.Subtitle: LAUNCHFUEL_SUB
FRIGATE_FUEL_3.Description_Text:
A huge barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

FRIG_BOOST_TRA.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_TRA_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_TRA.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_TRA.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

The mind control device plugs into the ship's trading and communications systems, allowing the Fleet Commander to gain the upper hand in any negotiation.

FRIG_BOOST_EXP.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_EXP_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_EXP.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_EXP.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful analytic computer overclocks the existing fleet systems, allowing for faster-than-light calculations. Heat is a problem, and the chips do not last long.

FRIG_BOOST_MIN.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_MIN_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_MIN.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_MIN.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

The mineral compressor allows fleet mining crews to liquidise the substances they extract, for both faster processing and easier transportation.

FRIG_BOOST_COM.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_COM_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_COM.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_COM.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This pack of autonomous explosives have been programmed to launch from the fleet and pilot themselves directly towards hostile vessels. Extremely dangerous.

FRIG_BOOST_SPD.Name: UI_FRIG_BOOST_SPD_NAME
FRIG_BOOST_SPD.Subtitle: FRIG_BOOST_SUB
FRIG_BOOST_SPD.Description_Text:
A <COMMODITY>temporary frigate upgrade<> that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful fuel upgrade overloads frigate engines, allowing for faster-than-usual travel.

FARMPROD1.Name: UI_FARMPROD_1_NAME
FARMPROD1.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD1.Description_Text:
Dilute acid for high current generation in diverse power cells.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Mordite<> and <TRADEABLE>Fungal Mould<>.

FARMPROD2.Name: UI_FARMPROD_2_NAME
FARMPROD2.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD2.Description_Text:
A synthetic lubricant that reduces wear and prolongs the lifespan of technologies with moving parts.

Crafted from <FUEL>Faecium<> and <TRADEABLE>Gamma Root<>.

FARMPROD3.Name: UI_FARMPROD_3_NAME
FARMPROD3.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD3.Description_Text:
Shatter-proof, scratch-resistant glass with a self-cleaning, UV-cured coating, for general construction use.

Refined from <STELLAR>Silicate<> powder. Extract silicate from the earth with a <TECHNOLOGY>Terrain Manipulator<>.

Can be crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Frost Crystals<> extracted from plants on <TECHNOLOGY>frozen<> worlds.

FARMPROD4.Name: UI_FARMPROD_4_NAME
FARMPROD4.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD4.Description_Text:
A thermal regulator produced from refined organic material. It is unique in its ability to produce, dissipate and distribute heat as required.

Crafted from <SPECIAL>Solanium<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Frost Crystals<>.

FARMPROD5.Name: UI_FARMPROD_5_NAME
FARMPROD5.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD5.Description_Text:
A connective fibre for electronics, made from an advanced synthetic polymer and capable of serving as a conduit for power and data.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Cactus Flesh<> and <TRADEABLE>Star Bulbs<>.

FARMPROD6.Name: UI_FARMPROD_6_NAME
FARMPROD6.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD6.Description_Text:
A highly reactive gel, this substance is both energy-rich and dangerous to touch.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Cactus Flesh<>.

FARMPROD7.Name: UI_FARMPROD_7_NAME
FARMPROD7.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD7.Description_Text:
A general purpose high explosive, offered in liquid form for convenience of transport and deployment. Do not drink.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Acid<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Unstable Gel<>.

FARMPROD8.Name: UI_FARMPROD_8_NAME
FARMPROD8.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD8.Description_Text:
An advanced building material, this glass has been imbued with organic compounds that allow it to react to the environment. Microbes within the glass filter harmful light of all wavelengths and balance the atmosphere as required.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Lubricant<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Glass<>.

FARMPROD9.Name: UI_FARMPROD_9_NAME
FARMPROD9.Subtitle: UI_FARMPROD_SUBTITLE
FARMPROD9.Description_Text:
Stackable, semi-flexible circuit board made from a highly durable synthetic polymer.

Crafted from <COMMODITY>Heat Capacitors<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Poly Fibre<>.

REACTION1.Name: UI_REACTION_1_NAME
REACTION1.Subtitle: UI_REACTION_SUBTITLE
REACTION1.Description_Text:
A refined product, holding the energy potential of heated atmospheric gas in a stable state until required.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Sulphurine<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

REACTION2.Name: UI_REACTION_2_NAME
REACTION2.Subtitle: UI_REACTION_SUBTITLE
REACTION2.Description_Text:
A refined product, taking ordinary carbon and boosting it with radioactive energy.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Radon<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

REACTION3.Name: UI_REACTION_3_NAME
REACTION3.Subtitle: UI_REACTION_SUBTITLE
REACTION3.Description_Text:
A refined product, this is a powerful organic fertiliser in an easily distributed form.

Crafted from <TRADEABLE>Nitrogen<> and <FUEL>Condensed Carbon<>.

COMPOUND1.Name: UI_COMPOUND_1_NAME
COMPOUND1.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND1.Description_Text:
A catalytic material used in the creation of many organic fertilisers.

Crafted from <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<> and <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<>.

COMPOUND2.Name: UI_COMPOUND_2_NAME
COMPOUND2.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND2.Description_Text:
An advanced material useful in many electronic devices, with its own in-built temperature regulator.

Crafted from <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

COMPOUND3.Name: UI_COMPOUND_3_NAME
COMPOUND3.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND3.Description_Text:
A paradoxical material, made less mysterious by its relative ease of manufacture.

Crafted from <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

COMPOUND4.Name: UI_COMPOUND_4_NAME
COMPOUND4.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND4.Description_Text:
An advanced fuel source, made from a perfect blend of high potential energy organic materials.

Crafted from <FUEL>Organic Catalyst<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Nitrogen Salt<>.

COMPOUND5.Name: UI_COMPOUND_5_NAME
COMPOUND5.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND5.Description_Text:
An advanced conductive material, the superconductor further enriches the field-warping power of the Semiconductor.

Crafted from <FUEL>Enriched Carbon<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Semiconductors<>.

COMPOUND6.Name: UI_COMPOUND_6_NAME
COMPOUND6.Subtitle: UI_COMPOUND_SUBTITLE
COMPOUND6.Description_Text:
An advanced, self-regulating hybrid material, the Cryo-Pump distributes heat across itself with near perfect efficiency, making it vital in the creation of thermal regulators.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Hot Ice<> and <FUEL>Thermic Condensate<>

MEGAPROD1.Name: UI_MEGAPROD_1_NAME
MEGAPROD1.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MEGAPROD1.Description_Text:
A miniature self-controlled nuclear reactor. Generates sub-stellar levels of energy in a hassle-free, widely compatible fuel module.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Liquid Explosives<> and <FUEL>Fusion Accelerant<>.

MEGAPROD2.Name: UI_MEGAPROD_2_NAME
MEGAPROD2.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MEGAPROD2.Description_Text:
A highly advanced computational device, essential for the complex calculations involved in warp travel.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Circuit Boards<> and <TECHNOLOGY>Superconductors<>.

MEGAPROD3.Name: UI_MEGAPROD_3_NAME
MEGAPROD3.Subtitle: UI_MEGAPROD_SUBTITLE
MEGAPROD3.Description_Text:
A low temperature chamber, designed to prevent the natural decay of organic matter.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Living Glass<> and a <TECHNOLOGY>Cryo-Pump<>.

ULTRAPROD1.Name: UI_ULTRAPROD_1_NAME
ULTRAPROD1.Subtitle: UI_ULTRAPROD_SUBTITLE
ULTRAPROD1.Description_Text:
A highly advanced piece of technology for use in the next generation of power plants. Producing a fusion core requires both intricate scientific skills and complex industrial processes.

Crafted from <FUEL>Portable Reactor<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Quantum Processors<> and <SPECIAL>Geodesite<>.

ULTRAPROD2.Name: UI_ULTRAPROD_2_NAME
ULTRAPROD2.Subtitle: UI_ULTRAPROD_SUBTITLE
ULTRAPROD2.Description_Text:
A device specifically crafted to keep lifeforms alive for thousands of years longer than their natural lifespan. Such a device requires great skill to manufacture, as not only is it technically complex, but the consequences for a user in the event of malfunction would be disastrous.

Crafted from <TECHNOLOGY>Quantum Processors<>, <TECHNOLOGY>Cryogenic Chambers<>, and <SPECIAL>Iridesite<>.

ATLAS_SEED_1.Name: ATLAS_SEED_1_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_1.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_1.Description_Text: Atlas Seed containing zonally-shifted quasi-stellar substrate. Warning: do not allow matrix to commune with this dimensional space.

ATLAS_SEED_2.Name: ATLAS_SEED_2_NAME
ATLAS_SEED_2.Subtitle: ATLAS_SEED_SUBTITLE
ATLAS_SEED_2.Description_Text: This Atlas Shell holds the remains of a parasitic space-borne lifeform, most likely of extra-dimensional origins.

"We Blight this new galaxy, as we did the last, as we will the next!"

S15_MESSAGE0.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE0.Description_Text:
A message recovered from a bottle stowed beneath the seat of the starship. It reads:

<VAL_ON>"I finally feel like I'm getting closer. A trader on Gisto offered me solid-gold information on its location, for a price.
And so I'm selling my ship. I'll miss the <VAL_ON>Celeste<>, but I have to know if the rumours are true. I hope whoever buys you takes good care of you..."
%PARTY_1%<>

S15_MESSAGE1.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE1.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE1.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"The rumours were true. It's out there, I can feel it. Not here, but somewhere. The water calls to me, I just need to follow its voice..."
%PARTY_3%<>

S15_MESSAGE2.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE2.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE2.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"I saw it in my dreams last night. Scales like fire and eyes of pure starlight. It sang to me, a song of hope and longing. It wants me to find it, I know it. I must be closing in."
%PARTY_4%<>

S15_MESSAGE3.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE3.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE3.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"I was right! It was here! After all these light years, all the doubts, it's finally mine. Oh, and how it shines! Like fire in the water, beautiful, impossible..."
%PARTY_5%<>

S15_MESSAGE4.Name: UI_S15_BOTTLED_MESSAGE_NAME
S15_MESSAGE4.Subtitle: UI_FISH_TRASH_SUB
S15_MESSAGE4.Description_Text:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

<VAL_ON>"The fire has faded from my catch's scales, and my dreams have soured. I thrash through the night. My skin itches, damp and clammy. Salt seeps from my pores.
It longs to be free. I cannot keep it contained like this. It must be free.
I must be free..."<>

S15_FISH.Name: UI_S15_FISH_NAME
S15_FISH.Subtitle: UI_FISH_LEGEND_SUB

Fire dances across the scales of this impossible marine being. Its starlit eyes stare back at you with a meaning far deeper than any fish should know. As they stare, the world around you fades away.

The sound of water fills your ears. It wants to be free. You want to be free...

DECAL_BONESOUP.Description_Text:

DECAL_EXTINCT.Description_Text:

This decal depicts a stylised planet and orbiting moon.

DECAL_BONEJUDGE.Name: BLD_DECAL_P_BONEJUDGE_NAME
DECAL_BONEJUDGE.Subtitle: BLD_DECAL_SUBTITLE
DECAL_BONEJUDGE.Description_Text:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add flair and decoration to bases.
This decal judges the value of one bone against another.

DECAL_RUINMECH.Name: BLD_DECAL_P_RUINMECH_NAME
DECAL_RUINMECH.Subtitle: BLD_DECAL_SUBTITLE
DECAL_RUINMECH.Description_Text:
An exclusive placeable decal, to add flair and decoration to bases.
This decal depicts an ancient guardian of living stone, bound to defend the bones of the fallen.

BASE_ROBOTOY.Name: BLD_ROBOTTOY_NAME
BASE_ROBOTOY.Subtitle: BLD_ROBOTTOY_SUB
BASE_ROBOTOY.Description_Text:
A perfectly-programmed and error free drone.

This miniature robot will be a lively presence in your base, bringing joy, laughter and a constant low-level humming to your home.

BASE_TOYCUBE.Name: BLD_TOYCUBE_NAME
BASE_TOYCUBE.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_STATUE_SUB
BASE_TOYCUBE.Description_Text:
An exclusive decorative curiosity.

This precisely crafted gadget utilises a localised gravitational field, delighting and fascinating base visitors.

BASE_TOYSPHERE.Name: BLD_TOYSPHERE_NAME
BASE_TOYSPHERE.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_STATUE_SUB
BASE_TOYSPHERE.Description_Text:
An exclusive decorative curiosity for bases.

This gadget emits a spherical hologram, representative of one of the quintillions of celestial bodies populating the galaxies.

BASE_TOYJELLY.Name: BLD_TOYJELLY_NAME
BASE_TOYJELLY.Subtitle: BLD_TOYJELLY_DESC
BASE_TOYJELLY.Description_Text:
The captured essence of an abyssal horror, contained for scientific and decorative use.

The bounding forcefield is of the very highest quality. The companion cannot escape. The companion will not escape. Escape.

BASE_TREE01.Name: BLD_TREE_1_NAME
BASE_TREE01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TREE01.Description_Text:
A large decorative fruit tree.

Fruit form, toxicity and existence will vary according to local climatic and pollinator conditions.

BASE_TREE02.Name: BLD_TREE_2_NAME
BASE_TREE02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TREE02.Description_Text:
A thin, non-fruiting tree. Root system is integrated with highly-adapted fungal symbiotes.

Supplied with its own mushrooms for ease of establishment. Fungus is non-toxic and non-spreading.

BASE_TREE03.Name: BLD_TREE_3_NAME
BASE_TREE03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TREE03.Description_Text:
A hardy evergreen tree, able to survive in a wide-range of climates.

Waxy leaves with a silvery underside provide excellent light harvesting abilities, as well as year-round interest and colour.

BASE_MEDPLANT01.Name: BLD_MEDPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_MEDPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_MEDPLANT01.Description_Text:
A medium-sized decorative plant. Each of its leaves is covered in a thin film of sticky latex. Insects that land on these leaves are slowly absorbed by digestive hormones mixed in with the glue.

Avoid accidental skin contact.

BASE_MEDPLANT02.Name: BLD_MEDPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_MEDPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_MEDPLANT02.Description_Text:
A squat, easily-managed form of the larger palm species.

Place outdoors to attract wildlife and to purify the air.

BASE_MEDPLANT03.Name: BLD_MEDPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_MEDPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_MEDPLANT03.Description_Text:
Sprouting decorative corn. Comes in a variety of colours. May attract decorative wildlife.

Unable to reproduce naturally. Must be hand-pollinated.

BASE_AQUARIUM.Name: BLD_AQUARIUM_NAME
BASE_AQUARIUM.Subtitle: BLD_AQUARIUM_SUBTITLE
BASE_AQUARIUM.Description_Text:
A small observatory unit for studying aquatic behaviours.

Completely self-contained, with its own renewable energy source, pump array, and self-cleaning filtration systems.

BASE_WPLANT1.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_WPLANT1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT1.Description_Text: A delicate marine invertebrate, cultivated for potted growth. Its distinctive looping structure gives it an attractive whimsical appearance.

BASE_WPLANT2.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_WPLANT2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT2.Description_Text: An eye-catching cluster of crystallised oceanic minerals. These crystals grow in a shard-like structure, and feature an unusual marbled colouration.

BASE_WPLANT3.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_WPLANT3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT3.Description_Text: A striking plant featuring luminescent, orb-shaped flowers. This domestic variety has adapted to absorb and process oxygen from any source, whether growing on land or underwater.

BASE_WPLANT4.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_4_NAME
BASE_WPLANT4.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT4.Description_Text: A carnivorous marine organism. An armoured shell encloses the core polyp, exposing only the stinging tentacles. Involuntary nerve spasms cause the creature to writhe perpetually: always seeking, always hungering.

BASE_WPLANT5.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_5_NAME
BASE_WPLANT5.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT5.Description_Text: A giant calcium formation, naturally configured into a strip of non-orientable space. Adds a mysterious deep-sea quality to any habitable base.

BASE_WPLANT6.Name: BLD_WATERPLANT_6_NAME
BASE_WPLANT6.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_WPLANT6.Description_Text: A rock formation pulled from the floor of a densely-populated ocean. The attached marine life is lacquered in a nutrient-rich mucus, to keep it fed and moist in terrestrial conditions.

BASE_BARNACLE.Name: BLD_BARNACLE_NAME
BASE_BARNACLE.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_BARNACLE.Description_Text:
A tenacious arthropod, naturally found encrusting stationary or slow-moving underwater objects.

This variety can be encouraged to affix itself to a chosen position, adding an aged marine appearance to bases.

BASE_TOYCORE.Name: BLD_TOYCORE_NAME
BASE_TOYCORE.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_STATUE_SUB
BASE_TOYCORE.Description_Text:
An exclusive decorative curiosity for bases.

A model of reality itself, as viewed from the perspective of an impossible observer. Infinite levels of detail wait to be discovered by the viewer with a powerful enough lens.

BASE_TERRARIUM.Name: BLD_TERRARIUM_NAME
BASE_TERRARIUM.Subtitle: BLD_TERRARIUM_SUBTITLE
BASE_TERRARIUM.Description_Text:
A small observatory unit for studying animal behaviours.

Completely self-contained, complete with inbuilt nutrient processor, air purifier and faecal disposal system.

BASE_HOTPLANT01.Name: BLD_HOTPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_HOTPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOTPLANT01.Description_Text:
A large-leafed, heat resistant tree.

Its broad fronds are laced with minerals, forming a protective barrier against the harsh sunlight of its native conditions.

BASE_HOTPLANT02.Name: BLD_HOTPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_HOTPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOTPLANT02.Description_Text:
A thin tree with a large, fleshy root system, well adapted to hot climates.

Root bulb may be tapped for a source of drinkable liquid, but this is not advised outside of the most dire circumstances.

BASE_HOTPLANT03.Name: BLD_HOTPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_HOTPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOTPLANT03.Description_Text: A garden module, complete with decorative mineral formation and built-in capillary matting for optimum humidity control.

BASE_RADPLANT01.Name: BLD_RADPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_RADPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_RADPLANT01.Description_Text:
A native of radioactive worlds, this curiously meaty succulent seems to sway gently even when the air is still...

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_RADPLANT02.Name: BLD_RADPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_RADPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_RADPLANT02.Description_Text:
This decorative tree has evolved to cope with high levels of background radiation. Its central glowing core attracts wildlife and is in no way a sense organ. It does not watch you.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_RADPLANT03.Name: BLD_RADPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_RADPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_RADPLANT03.Description_Text:
This beautiful statement tree thrives in the heat of intense gamma radiation. To ensure survival in non-native environments, a chunk of high-energy material has been embedded in the trunk.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_TOXPLANT01.Name: BLD_TOXPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_TOXPLANT01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TOXPLANT01.Description_Text:
This swollen protuberance grows rapidly from a fine network of underground spores. Greatly improves nearby soil quality.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_TOXPLANT02.Name: BLD_TOXPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_TOXPLANT02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TOXPLANT02.Description_Text:
While this plant can be cultivated as a crop, consumption is not advised.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_TOXPLANT03.Name: BLD_TOXPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_TOXPLANT03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_TOXPLANT03.Description_Text:
This delightful architectural floral combines two highly popular aesthetics: wriggling tentacles and giant fungi.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_DUSTPLANT1.Name: BLD_DUSTPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_DUSTPLANT1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_DUSTPLANT1.Description_Text:
Elegant feathery filaments run around this desert plant, increasing the surface area for moisture absorption. They also look very fetching.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_DUSTPLANT2.Name: BLD_DUSTPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_DUSTPLANT2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_DUSTPLANT2.Description_Text:
Delightful succulent baubles, these lovely plants top their bulbous bodies with a show of beautiful flowers.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_DUSTPLANT3.Name: BLD_DUSTPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_DUSTPLANT3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_DUSTPLANT3.Description_Text:
The bark on this tree is misleading. Neither rough nor hard, its flesh is instead soft and moist to the touch. Wrinkles in the surface store extra water for times of hardship.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_COLDPLANT1.Name: BLD_COLDPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_COLDPLANT1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_COLDPLANT1.Description_Text:
This tough conifer pumps its sap with anti-freezing enzymes, allowing it to survive unimaginably low temperatures.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_COLDPLANT2.Name: BLD_COLDPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_COLDPLANT2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_COLDPLANT2.Description_Text:
A snow-filled stone trough. This is the perfect home for the small, tough plants that grow on ice-bound worlds.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_COLDPLANT3.Name: BLD_COLDPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_COLDPLANT3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_COLDPLANT3.Description_Text:
This tree lives on an almost geological time scale. Low heat and light levels in their native habitat restrict growth to mere millimeters each season. A sample this size is a botanical marvel.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_ROCK01.Name: BLD_ROCK_1_NAME
BASE_ROCK01.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_ROCK01.Description_Text:
A pleasing mineral formation, crystalised from oceanic salts. May also contain aquatic fossils and/or lifeforms.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_ROCK02.Name: BLD_ROCK_2_NAME
BASE_ROCK02.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_ROCK02.Description_Text:
A remarkable piece of geological geometry. A stable load-bearing arch, infused with curiously angular solid geodes.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_ROCK03.Name: BLD_ROCK_3_NAME
BASE_ROCK03.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_ROCK03.Description_Text:
Once a discarded byproduct of deep-level crystal mining, the aesthetic value of the rocks is now better appreciated.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_SWAMP1.Name: BLD_SWAMPPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_SWAMP1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_SWAMP1.Description_Text:
This species of fungus is notable for its dense capillary network and bioluminescent qualities. A circulating chain of chemical reactions produces the toadstool's nocturnal glow.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_SWAMP2.Name: BLD_SWAMPPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_SWAMP2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_SWAMP2.Description_Text:
This ancient stump was harvested from a clonal tree colony, estimated to have lived for over a hundred millennia. Its bark releases a pleasant mossy fragrance.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_SWAMP3.Name: BLD_SWAMPPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_SWAMP3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_SWAMP3.Description_Text:
This simple mud hut was modelled after a mysterious structure discovered in the mists of planet Saxm A13. Similar structures have been found throughout the universe, with no proven hypothesis regarding their origin.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_HOUDINI1.Name: BLD_HOUDINIPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_HOUDINI1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOUDINI1.Description_Text:
A proteinous formation of unknown origin, replicated aboard the Space Anomaly. Its skeletal structure often retains pockets of air, leading to slightly warmer or cooler temperatures in the centre of the cage.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_HOUDINI2.Name: BLD_HOUDINIPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_HOUDINI2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOUDINI2.Description_Text:
This unusual lifeform, dominated by a wheel of photophore glands, is difficult to classify neatly into flora or fauna. The thick columns of thorns help protect the flavoursome glands from predators.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_HOUDINI3.Name: BLD_HOUDINIPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_HOUDINI3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_HOUDINI3.Description_Text:
The eye-like protrusions on this bizarre organism are capable of both processing light and performing simple calculations, although it is unclear what they are watching for...

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_INFEST1.Name: BLD_INFESTEDPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_INFEST1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_INFEST1.Description_Text:
This eggshell still whispers a faint song, as though connected to a distant chorus...

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_INFEST2.Name: BLD_INFESTEDPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_INFEST2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_INFEST2.Description_Text:
The broad, plate-like leaf topping this tree is highly efficient for photosynthesis, and wild specimens can grow to extraordinary heights. This domestic variety is cultivated to be suitable to furnish habitations.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_INFEST3.Name: BLD_INFESTEDPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_INFEST3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_INFEST3.Description_Text:
This vegetative structure is high in antioxidants, though a thick layer of scales makes it impractical for farming.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_LAVA1.Name: BLD_LAVAPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_LAVA1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_LAVA1.Description_Text:
A quiet roar sounds from within this natural crystal formation, lava and gas dancing in a perpetual cycle of heating and solidifying. Mesmerising to the eye, but despite the ultrahot core, only slightly warm to the touch.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_LAVA2.Name: BLD_LAVAPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_LAVA2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_LAVA2.Description_Text:
This hybrid of egg and rock is known to form around the larvae of certain species, keeping the vulnerable creature warm and protected as it develops over the course of several decades. Membranous splits in the rock's surface expose the ever-shifting molten heart.

Provides decorative landscaping opportunities for bases.

BASE_LAVA3.Name: BLD_LAVAPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_LAVA3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_LAVA3.Description_Text:
Although primitive in design, this habitation heater is nonetheless a popular home furnishing. Its hypnotic flames and gentle crackling lend a comforting ambience to any room.

Provides interior decoration opportunities for bases.

BASE_CAVE1.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_1_NAME
BASE_CAVE1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE1.Description_Text: This fungal growth, identifiable by its wide, smooth cap and luminescent pores, is native to a variety of cave biomes. Saucer Fungi enjoy a symbiotic relationship with many species of burrowing creatures.

BASE_CAVE2.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_2_NAME
BASE_CAVE2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE2.Description_Text: A hardy variety of lampenflora. This creeping vine occurs naturally in damp, subterranean environments, but will thrive as a free-standing shrub in any biome type.

BASE_CAVE3.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_3_NAME
BASE_CAVE3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE3.Description_Text: This attractive glowing flower is remarkable for its scent, reminiscent of freshly tilled soil. Due to the plant's mineral-rich diet, the stamens often contain traces of cobalt.

BASE_CAVE4.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_4_NAME
BASE_CAVE4.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE4.Description_Text: Clusters of these large mushrooms can be found growing in underground caves. The surface 'veins' form part of an unusual gill structure, releasing spores from both above and below the fungus's cap.

BASE_CAVE5.Name: BLD_CAVEPLANT_5_NAME
BASE_CAVE5.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_CAVE5.Description_Text: This stalagmite was formed by the dripping of cobalt-rich moisture over several millennia. It is eternally cold to the touch, as though the rock recalls the temperature of its home cave.

BASE_NEXUS1.Name: BLD_NEXUSPROP_1_NAME
BASE_NEXUS1.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_NEXUS_PROP_SUB
BASE_NEXUS1.Description_Text: This spiked chamber contains a globule of antimatter, creating an unusual display piece for discerning base builders.

BASE_NEXUS2.Name: BLD_NEXUSPROP_2_NAME
BASE_NEXUS2.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_NEXUS_PROP_SUB
BASE_NEXUS2.Description_Text:
A replica of the mysterious orb utilised by Polo's Quicksilver Synthesis Companion.

The physical properties of the orb are forever shifting in strangely rhythmic patterns: temperature, radioactivity and density all fluctuating to an unheard song.

BASE_NEXUS3.Name: BLD_NEXUSPROP_3_NAME
BASE_NEXUS3.Subtitle: UI_SPECIAL_NEXUS_PROP_SUB
BASE_NEXUS3.Description_Text: A miniaturised replica of the bubbling 'liquid' vat which forms part of the Space Anomaly's anatomy. This mesmerising ornament brings an echo of Polo and Nada's anomalous home to planetary bases.

BASE_BUBPIPE.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_MAGIC_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'.

Intelligently welds into <SPECIAL>different shapes<> to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_S.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_S.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_S.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_L.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_L_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_L.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_L.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This L-shaped configuration allows for curves in duct connections.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_T.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_T_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_T.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_T.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This T-shaped configuration allows for creating branches in duct connections.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

BASE_BUBPIPE_X.Name: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_X_NAME
BASE_BUBPIPE_X.Subtitle: BLD_BUBBLE_PIPE_SUB
BASE_BUBPIPE_X.Description_Text:
This clear glass aqueduct encloses a perpetually churning supply of 'liquid'. This X-shaped configuration allows for connecting four ducts in a cruciform arrangement.

Weld together with different duct shapes to create mesmerising displays in your base.

S_SAIL0.Name: BLD_S_SAIL0_NAME
S_SAIL0.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE

BUILDCHAIR4.Subtitle: BLD_CHAIR_SUBTITLE
BUILDCHAIR4.Description_Text: A sturdy, well-constructed seat, standardised for installation in Space Stations across the galaxies. Its angular design is surprisingly ergonomic.

PLANTPOT4.Subtitle: BLD_DECOR_SUBTITLE

BASE_GRASS1.Name: BLD_GRASS_1_NAME
BASE_GRASS1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS1.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. This variety is characterised by very long, thin blades, covered in very fine hairs.

BASE_GRASS2.Name: BLD_GRASS_2_NAME
BASE_GRASS2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS2.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. This variety, like its taller cousin, is characterised by long hirsute blades - but grows more densely, with slightly heftier blades.

BASE_GRASS3.Name: BLD_GRASS_3_NAME
BASE_GRASS3.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS3.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. The wide, flat blades secrete a fragrant, unpleasant-tasting sap to deter predators.

BASE_GRASS4.Name: BLD_GRASS_4_NAME
BASE_GRASS4.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS4.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. This variety features attractively curled blades, which furl and unfurl to allow the plant to maintain a constant internal temperature.

BASE_GRASS5.Name: BLD_GRASS_5_NAME
BASE_GRASS5.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS5.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. Closely related to certain varieties of seaweed, ribbon grass can be identified by its long rippling blades and fine hexagonal surface texture.

BASE_GRASS6.Name: BLD_GRASS_6_NAME
BASE_GRASS6.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS6.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. Cloven paw bears more structural similarity to a shrub than a true grass, and features large glossy leaves for rapid photosynthesis.

BASE_GRASS7.Name: BLD_GRASS_7_NAME
BASE_GRASS7.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB
BASE_GRASS7.Description_Text: A tough ornamental grass, suitable for growing in all biomes, soil types, and weather conditions. The branching blades of this variety are formed of woody, twig-like armour insulating thick veins of moisture-storing resin.

BASE_FLOWER1.Name: BLD_FLOWER_1_NAME
BASE_FLOWER1.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB

BASE_FLOWER2.Name: BLD_FLOWER_2_NAME
BASE_FLOWER2.Subtitle: BLD_FLORA_SUB

BASE_FLOWER3.Name: BLD_FLOWER_3_NAME
